disabling some features such as Exploration or Terrain.


HOW TO INSTALL THIS GAME:
=========================

Just toss it on your hard drive somewhere!  (But don't try to install
it on top of an old version.  Put it in a fresh empty dir.)

Thats it!...

You do not need to copy any files to LIBS: or FONTS: or anywhere else!

You do not need to edit your startup-sequence!

You do not need to make any ASSIGNs!

There are no other files that you have to mess with!

You do not need to run any install scripts or answer any complicated
questions!

If you want to delete the game then just delete its dir and it will be
gone.  You do not have to "uninstall" any files! (since no files are ever
"installed" anywhere.)


All software should be this easy to install, don't you agree?

NOTE: DO NOT USE LHA V2.1!  It is bugged!  Use lha v1.x.
There are over 5000 files in this archive.  Lha v2.x will choke and drown
in its own vomit.  Use Lha v1.x!

WARNING! The very first time you run the game, the game must decompress
1000 audio files.  This will take several minutes but is only done the
very first time you play the game.  We apologize for the delay but this
allows us to reduce the size of the lha archive by 7.5 megs in v5.20.

We recommend that you reset your computer before running the game the
first time.  This will defrag your ram and guarantee a perfect startup
with no problems.

If you don't reset first then you may have 256 megs of ram, which is more
than enough, but due to all the software you have been running all day,
your ram may be fragmented into 1000s of small chunks, which might stop
the game from running.




         Total Chaos: Battle at the Frontier of Time
         -------------------------------------------

Once upon a time, in the long ago days of yesteryear there was a rule
that each and every computer game was infused with a magical
substance before its release.  Over the years this substance became
more and more rare until finally it was nearly extinct.  Many games
manufacturers began substituting other ingredients in place of the
magic one.  They began to substitute "3D Graphics" and "Mpeg Movies"
into their games.  This fooled many people, but not everyone.

Then one day some brave and daring game designers went on an
expedition to find an unlimited supply of the lost magic
ingredient.  It was in a darkened basement stored in a dusty old
box labeled "Gameplay".

Total Chaos:  Battle at the Frontier of Time is the game they
created with the magical ingredient.  It hearkens back to a
different time.  A time of play mechanics and fun seasoned with
balance and drowned in a thousand liters of the Magic Sauce of
Replayability.


Total Chaos is infinite.


History:
--------

Ok folks, this is a game about war.  War invariably causes collateral
damage.  Years ago back in Chaos Wizard War I most of the collateral
damage was concentrated in the 3rd dimension, resulting in its
destruction.  Oops sorry about that. :)  The first 2 dimensions are
still in good working order though.  Its a good thing because this
means all the gamepieces are large, flat and easily identifiable.
There's none of that "Oh my sheep was hidden behind some trees and I
couldn't see it!" stuff in Total Chaos.



What is this game about?
------------------------

The world of Total Chaos is a small 2 dimensional battlefield, all
that is left of the world since the Decades of Magewar between
Conwell the Conquerer and Incredible Irvine and all their demonic
servants.  The magical energies tormented time and space and ripped
reality out of the world.  Some wizards escaped into sub-space and
survived the Global Thermomagical Devastation.  Now they come back
into a world of Total Chaos, a world with only one rule:  The
smartest one wins.  The battle does not know morality or loyalty.
Phyisical laws can be bent or broken.  The borders of time and
space became weak.  A strong will can achieve everything.  The will
of a wizard.  Eight wizards that change the world in different
directions.  Eight wills that fight for domination, not caring
about any result beside victory.





What sort of game is this?
--------------------------

Total Chaos is a turn-based, fantasy strategy game of Monsters &
Magic, Swords & Sorcery, Wizards & Warriors, Death & Destruction,
Demons & Dungeons, Ghouls & Ghosts, etc.

It isn't too complicated like many wargames can be and it isn't
overly simplistic like many boardgames can be.

Note from the Explosionographer:
It simply offers you Total freedom to do anything you can at any time you
may.  There is such a vast range of possibilities that no one knows them
all.  And the more you know, the more you want.

Total Chaos is a Multitasking AmigaOS game featuring tons of gameplay
options.  You can play against the computer or against humans or
both.  Every man for himself or in teams.  The choice is yours.




